<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="149" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,543,1290]" box="[151,504,543,570]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<typeStatus box="[151,207,544,570]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Type</typeStatus>
locality: “Chab[arovsk].”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,543,1290]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Present status: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Butler, 1878)" baseAuthorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[364,763,579,606]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Neoploca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arctipennis">
<emphasis box="[364,602,580,606]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Neoploca arctipennis</emphasis>
(Butler, 1878)
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authority="(Graeser, 1888)" baseAuthorityName="Graeser" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[798,1433,580,606]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Neoploca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arctipennis" subSpecies="nigrofascicula">
<emphasis box="[798,1035,580,606]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Neoploca arctipennis</emphasis>
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[1089,1250,580,606]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">nigrofascicula</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Graeser, L." box="[1263,1424,580,606]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" pagination="33 - 153" refId="ref6673" refString="Graeser, L. (1888) Beitrage zur Kenntniss der Lepidopteren-Fauna des Amurlandes. Berliner entomologische Zeitschrift, 32, 33 - 153. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 47918880407" type="journal article" year="1888">Graeser, 1888</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
: Demopsestini.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,543,1290]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Taxonomic remarks: The taxon is better considered a continental geographic subspecies of the Japanese 
<taxonomicName authority="(Butler, 1878)" baseAuthorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityYear="1878" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Neoploca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arctipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">N. arctipennis</emphasis>
(Butler, 1878)
</taxonomicName>
although to date it has been listed only as its synonym.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,543,1290]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Nomenclatural notes: A 
<typeStatus box="[477,580,723,749]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Graeser, 1888" authorityName="Graeser" authorityYear="1888" box="[621,1061,724,750]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Asphalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrofascicula">
<emphasis box="[621,891,724,750]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Asphalia nigrofascicula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Graeser, L." box="[900,1061,724,750]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" pagination="33 - 153" refId="ref6673" refString="Graeser, L. (1888) Beitrage zur Kenntniss der Lepidopteren-Fauna des Amurlandes. Berliner entomologische Zeitschrift, 32, 33 - 153. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 47918880407" type="journal article" year="1888">Graeser, 1888</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, was designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Laszlo, G. M. &amp; Ronkay, G. &amp; Ronkay, L. &amp; Witt, T." pageId="4" pageNumber="149" pagination="1 - 683" refId="ref6734" refString="Laszlo, G. M., Ronkay, G., Ronkay, L. &amp; Witt, T. (2007) The Thyatiridae of Eurasia Including the Sundaland and New Guinea (Lepidoptera). Esperiana, 13, 1 - 683." type="journal article" year="2007">
László 
<emphasis box="[1377,1429,724,750]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">&amp; al</emphasis>
. (2007: 284)
</bibRefCitation>
: this was a 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[427,485,760,786]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">male</emphasis>
specimen from 
<collectionCode box="[673,754,760,786]" country="Libya" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/49nc-28y0" name="Natural History Museum, Tripoli" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">NHML</collectionCode>
labeled “Ussuri. Dörr[ies]. 
<collectingRegion box="[1075,1151,759,785]" country="Germany" name="Berlin" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Berlin</collectingRegion>
”. The authors added that “there are no authentic specimens of this taxon in 
<collectingRegion box="[717,787,795,821]" country="Germany" name="Berlin" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Berlin</collectingRegion>
while in the collection in 
<collectingRegion box="[1083,1240,795,822]" country="Russia" name="Saint Petersburg" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">St. Petersburg</collectingRegion>
there is only a 
<specimenCount box="[1415,1436,796,822]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
under the name ‘ 
<emphasis box="[340,510,832,858]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">nigrofascicula’</emphasis>
”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,543,1290]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2847265319" collectionCode="BMNH" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" specimenCount="1" specimenCount-female="1" typeStatus="syntype">
The taxon was in fact described “…nur in zwei 
<specimenCount box="[730,761,867,893]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" type="female">♀♀</specimenCount>
-Stücken, welche ich in Chab[arovsk]. aus … Puppen gezo- gen habe” (
<bibRefCitation author="Graeser, L." box="[282,503,903,930]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" pagination="33 - 153" refId="ref6673" refString="Graeser, L. (1888) Beitrage zur Kenntniss der Lepidopteren-Fauna des Amurlandes. Berliner entomologische Zeitschrift, 32, 33 - 153. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 47918880407" type="journal article" year="1888">Graeser, 1888: 152</bibRefCitation>
). On this basis the male from 
<collectionCode box="[849,933,904,930]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">BMNH</collectionCode>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[942,1018,903,930]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">cann’t</emphasis>
be a 
<typeStatus box="[1082,1169,904,930]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">syntype</typeStatus>
and thus 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1282,1358,903,930]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">cann’t</emphasis>
be the 
<typeStatus box="[151,254,939,965]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">lectotype</typeStatus>
of the taxon (Articles 74.2 and 74.1 of the Code)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,543,1290]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2847265304" collectionCode="ZISP" collectorName="Only &amp; L. Graeser &amp; Graeser" location="The" municipality="It" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" specimenCount="1" specimenCount-female="1" stateProvince="Khabarovsk" typeStatus="syntype">
<collectorName box="[199,255,975,1001]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Only</collectorName>
one female of those listed by 
<collectorName box="[591,709,976,1002]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">L. Graeser</collectorName>
is present in 
<collectionCode box="[858,915,976,1002]" country="Russia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/vmfx-g997" name="Zoological Institute, Russian Academy of Sciences" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">ZISP</collectionCode>
in fine condition, and is the only known original 
<typeStatus box="[192,279,1012,1038]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">syntype</typeStatus>
of the taxon which is designated 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[653,705,1012,1038]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">here</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[712,815,1011,1037]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Graeser, 1888" authorityName="Graeser" authorityYear="1888" box="[852,1284,1012,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Asphalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrofascicula">
<emphasis box="[852,1119,1012,1038]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Asphalia nigrofascicula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Graeser, L." box="[1125,1284,1012,1038]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" pagination="33 - 153" refId="ref6673" refString="Graeser, L. (1888) Beitrage zur Kenntniss der Lepidopteren-Fauna des Amurlandes. Berliner entomologische Zeitschrift, 32, 33 - 153. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 47918880407" type="journal article" year="1888">Graeser, 1888</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1295,1312,1012,1038]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">It</collectingMunicipality>
is a spread specimen in fine condition (coll. 
<collectionCode box="[515,574,1048,1074]" country="Russia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/vmfx-g997" name="Zoological Institute, Russian Academy of Sciences" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">ZISP</collectionCode>
) supplied with the following labels: a greenish elongated rectangle with a narrow black frame and printed «Chabarofka» [now the city of 
<collectingRegion box="[830,968,1083,1110]" country="Russia" name="Khabarovsk" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Khabarovsk</collectingRegion>
] and a white wider rectangle with narrow black frame and printed text «coll 
<emphasis box="[534,662,1120,1146]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Dieckmann</emphasis>
| (
<emphasis box="[690,782,1120,1146]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<collectorName box="[690,782,1120,1146]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Graeser</collectorName>
</emphasis>
legit)». 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03FCDF48915BFFD2F4FE6633086CFAC2:8E8A3885915BFFD2F703631D0EDFFBB2" box="[874,918,1119,1145]" municipality="It" name="The" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" stateProvince="Khabarovsk">The</location>
specimen was designated with a red rectangular label with printed text “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Hübner, 1821" authorityName="Nigrofascicula Graeser" authorityYear="1888" box="[454,554,1156,1182]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Asphalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[454,554,1156,1182]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Asphalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
| 
<taxonomicName authority="Graeser" authorityName="Graeser" authorityYear="1888" box="[573,830,1156,1182]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Asphalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrofascicula">
<emphasis box="[573,734,1156,1182]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">nigrofascicula</emphasis>
Graeser
</taxonomicName>
, | 1888 
<specimenCount box="[916,937,1156,1182]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
| design. Dubatolov et | Zolotuhin, 1994”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,543,1290]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2847265314" collectionCode="V, ZISP" collectorName="The &amp; L. Graeser" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
Although the specimen was selected as a 
<typeStatus box="[681,784,1191,1217]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">lectotype</typeStatus>
in 1994 by 
<collectionCode box="[927,947,1192,1218]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
. Dubatolov and 
<collectionCode box="[1137,1157,1192,1218]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
. Zolotuhin, this was not published, and therefore it is officially designated only here by 
<collectionCode box="[856,876,1228,1254]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
. Mironov &amp; 
<collectionCode box="[1018,1038,1228,1254]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
. Zolotuhin. The specimen is kept in 
<collectionCode box="[151,208,1264,1290]" country="Russia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/vmfx-g997" name="Zoological Institute, Russian Academy of Sciences" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">ZISP</collectionCode>
in cabinet 217/drawer 20. 
<collectorName box="[507,551,1263,1289]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">The</collectorName>
second 
<typeStatus box="[643,730,1264,1290]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">syntype</typeStatus>
female mentioned by 
<collectorName box="[980,1098,1264,1290]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">L. Graeser</collectorName>
is not present here
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
